      <h2><small>14.</small>Life Below Water</h2>
      <h3>Zinc Contributes:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Zinc is a naturally occurring element in natural waters (surface-, ground-, and see water). Organisms living in
          water need zinc to survive.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>IZA Contributes:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>IZA initiates and coordinates targeted research projects to understand the mechanisms of zinc's presence in
          waters, in partnership with regulatory authorities when possible.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>IZA Member Contributes:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>The Srfjorden fjord adjacent to the Odda zinc smelter, which was once one of the most heavily polluted marine
          environments in the world, has been returned to almost pre-industrial conditions through a long-term commitment
          to environmental protection.</li>
        <li>In 2012, Teck committed $12.5 million to the Vancouver Aquarium in support of its conservation, research and
          education efforts to advance water stewardship. The funding helps provide educational programming and research
          focused on conservation issues principally related to water and aquatic habits.</li>
      </ul>
